						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the <hi rend="italic">mukha-maṇḍapa</hi> of the Talakaṇṭamma shrine.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1272, Piṅgaḷa, Āshāḍha ba. 11, Thursday,</hi> corresponding to 1350 A.D., June 30 (f.d.t. 97). However, the cyclic year is Vikṛita.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It refers to a certain Bēmareḍi Talajiya and Sirivōla Vallasāni. The purport of the inscription is not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
